The '''Administrative Council''' ({{lang-no|Administrasjonsrådet}}) was a council established by the [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court]] to govern [[Norway]]. The council of seven people was established on 15 April 1940, replacing [[Quisling's First Cabinet]], and was led by [[Ingolf Elster Christensen]]. It was replaced on 25 September by another council by [[Josef Terboven]], referred to in Norwegian as Josef Terboven's ''kommissariske statsråder''.
{|class=wikitable ! Member !! Portfolio |- | [[Ingolf Elster Christensen]] || Chair and responsible for issues related to the [[Norwegian Ministry of Foreign Affairs|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], the [[Norwegian Ministry of Defence|Ministry of Defence]] (limited to non-political and non-military matters), and from 4 June the [[Norwegian Ministry of Transport and Communications|Ministry of Labour]]. |- | [[Andreas Diesen]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Health and Social Affairs|Ministry of Social Affairs]] |- | [[Gunnar Jahn]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Health and Social Affairs|Ministry of Finance and Customs]] and until 4 June [[Norwegian Ministry of Transport and Communications|Ministry of Labour]] |- | [[Didrik Arup Seip]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Education and Research|Ministry of Education and Research]] |- | [[Ole F. Harbek]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Justice|Ministry of Justice]] |- | [[Jens Bache-Wiig]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Trade and Industry|Ministry of Trade and Industry]] and Ministry of Supplies |- | [[Rasmus Mork]] || [[Norwegian Ministry of Agriculture and Food|Ministry of Agriculture]] |}
