{{EngvarB|date=August 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox Newspaper |name = Business Day |image = |type = Daily [[newspaper]] |format = |foundation = 2001 |ceased publication = |price = |owners = |publisher = Frank Aigbogun |editor = Anthony Osae-Brown |language = English |circulation = |headquarters = [[Lagos]], [[Lagos State]], Nigeria |website = http://www.businessdayonline.com/ }}
'''''Business Day''''', established in 2001, is a daily business newspaper based in [[Lagos]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.columbia.edu/cu/lweb/indiv/africa/cuvl/NRonline.html |title=Nigeria Online News |publisher=Columbia University Libraries |accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref> It is the only [[Nigeria]]n newspaper with a bureau in [[Accra, Ghana]]. It has both daily and Sunday titles. It circulates in Nigeria and Ghana.
BusinessDay Media Ltd is the leading medium for up-to-date news and insightful analysis of business, policy and the economy in Nigeria. A critical decision-making tool for investors and managers. It provides unbiased news and informed analysis on politics, governance, social and economic trends.
The publisher is Frank Aigbogun, a former editor of the ''[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]]'' newspaper.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.diageoafricabusinessreportingawards.com/2006awards/video_frankaigbogun.htm |title=2006 Awards |publisher=Diageo |accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://64.182.81.172/webpages/features/enterprise/2008/feb/09/enterprise-09-02-2008-003.htm |work=Daily Sun |title=Our tourism heroes, past and present |date=9 February 2008 |accessdate=2011-05-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20110810205853/http://64.182.81.172/webpages/features/enterprise/2008/feb/09/enterprise-09-02-2008-003.htm |archivedate=10 August 2011 |df= }}</ref> The editor-in-chief is Onwuchekwa Jemie while the editor of the daily paper is Anthony Osae Brown. John Omachonu is the deputy editor of the daily title. Similarly, the editor of the Sunday title is Zebulon Agomuo while Chuks Oluigbo is his assistant. The newspaper has creative writers such as Obodo Ejiro, Iheanyi Nwachukwu, Patrick Atuanya, Onyinye Nwachukwu, Jumoke Akiyode, Chuka Uroko, Ifeoma Okeke, Hope Moses Ashike, Olusola Bello, Odinaka Anudu, Obinna Emelike, Teliat Sule, and Chuks Oluigbo, among others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessdayonline.com/NG/index.php/contact-us |title=Contact Us |publisher=''Business Day'' |accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref>
The newspaper has produced many award-winning journalists. Anthony Osae-Brown was a finalist for Best Business News Story in May 2011, a Diageo Africa Business Reporting Award.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.diageoafricabusinessreportingawards.com/press/ |title=Diageo Africa Business Reporting Awards 2011 - Finalists Announced |date=5 May 2011 |publisher=Diageo |accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref> Godwin Nnanna, a former assistant editor, has won several international journalism awards including gold and silver medals in UN Foundation Prize for humanitarian and development reporting, and the Elizabeth Neuffer Memorial Prize for written media.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.observer.ug/new/archives/2006arch/news/dec/news200612145.php |title=Godwin Nnanna |publisher=The Dag Hammarskjöld Scholarship Fund for Journalists |accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref>
Obodo Ejiro and Teliat Sule have both won the Citi Journalistic Award for excellence in financial journalism, while Iheanyi Nwachukwu and Patrick Atuanya won the Securities and Exchange Commission Capital Market Essay Competition in 2012 and 2013 respectively.
The newspaper worked with [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] on the "Most Respected Company and CEO" survey in 2006. Survey results showed the opinions of Nigerian CEOs. Awards based on the survey were presented in a ceremony in Lagos.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=A6OxK11RFDoC&pg=PA384 |page=384 |title=Corporate Reputation and the News Media: Agenda-Setting Within Business News Coverage in Developed, Emerging, and Frontier Markets |author=Craig E. Carroll |publisher=Taylor & Francis |year=2010 |ISBN=0-415-87153-0}}</ref> In February 2011, ''Business Day'' organized its annual Capital Market conference.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.nigeriamusicmovement.com/index.php/nigerian-bank-nigeria-nigerian-stock-exchange-foreign-investors-maintain-interest-in-nigerian-capital-market |archive-url = https://archive.is/20130130000549/http://www.nigeriamusicmovement.com/index.php/nigerian-bank-nigeria-nigerian-stock-exchange-foreign-investors-maintain-interest-in-nigerian-capital-market |dead-url = yes |archive-date = 2013-01-30 |title = Nigerian Bank Nigeria Nigerian Stock Exchange – Foreign Investors Maintain Interest In Nigerian Capital Market |work = [[Next (Nigeria)]] |date = February 2011 |accessdate = 2011-05-13 }}</ref> In March 2011 the newspaper organized the Business Day SME Forum 2011 in Lagos. The forum was attended by entrepreneurs, consultants, financiers and representatives from various industries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.connectnigeria.com/articles/connectnigeria-features-in-business-day-sme-forum-2011/270 |title=ConnectNigeria features in Business Day SME Forum 2011 |date=30 March 2011 |publisher=ConnectNigeria |accessdate=2011-05-13 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
