{{For|the metal band|Catuvolcus (band)}} '''Cativolcus''' or '''Catuvolcus''' (died 53 BC) was king of half of the country of the [[Eburones]], a people between the [[Meuse River|Meuse]] and [[Rhine]] rivers, united with [[Ambiorix]], the other king, in the insurrection against the [[Roman Republic|Romans]] in 54 BC; but when [[Julius Caesar]] in the next year proceeded to devastate the territories of the Eburones, Cativolcus, who was advanced in age and unable to endure the labours of war and flight, poisoned himself, after imprecating curses upon Ambiorix.<ref>{{cite book|title=Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities|editor=[[William Smith (lexicographer)|William Smith]]|year=1870|page=634|url=http://ancientlibrary.com/smith-bio/0643.html|access-date=2007-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060522223104/http://www.ancientlibrary.com/smith-bio/0643.html#|archive-date=2006-05-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
