{{Infobox film | name = Les Accords de Bella | image = Les_Accords_de_Bella_DVD_cover.jpg | caption = DVD cover | director = [[David Constantin]] | producer = Caméléon Production | writer = | starring = | distributor = | released = 2007 | runtime = 52 minutes | country = [[Mauritius]] | language = | budget = | gross = | screenplay = David Constantin | cinematography = Mahen Bujun | editing = David Constantin | music = Menwar }}
'''''Les Accords de Bella''''' is a 2007 anthropological documentary film directed by [[David Constantin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalfilmafriqueiles.fr/en/les-films/9.php|title=Les Accords de Bella|publisher=Festival Film Afriqueiles|accessdate=9 March 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120802194131/http://www.festivalfilmafriqueiles.fr/en/les-films/9.php|archivedate=2 August 2012|df=}}</ref> It was selected by the [[African Film Festival of Cordoba - FCAT]].
== Synopsis == [[Rodrigues Island]], lost in the middle of the [[Indian Ocean]], has something particular: There are more than 500 accordions for 35,000 people. Polkas, mazurkas and waltzes are part of the history and mestization of an island forgotten by all for a very long time. Here, the accordion is not a forgotten instrument, quite the contrary; its sound mixes with African drums so that young and old can dance. With Philippe Imbert's help, a French craftsman, the Rodrigues Accordion Association has set out on a new adventure: Making their own accordion. The first one, the prototype, completely made on the island, is called Bella.<ref name="Express">{{cite news | url=http://www.lexpress.mu/services/archive-90183-david-constantin--bella--au-bois-dormant.html | title=David Constantin, "Bella" au bois dormant | work=[[L'Express (France)]] | date=16 July 2007 | accessdate=March 10, 2012 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130219031304/http://www.lexpress.mu/services/archive-90183-david-constantin--bella--au-bois-dormant.html | archivedate=19 February 2013 | df= }}</ref><ref name=mauricien>{{cite news|title=Les accords de Bella|url=http://www.lemauricien.org/weekend/070715/mg.htm#4|accessdate=11 March 2012|newspaper=[[Le Mauricien]]|date=15 July 2007|language=French}}</ref>
