The '''Medical Association of Malta''' is a professional association for doctors in Malta.  It is affiliated to the [[World Medical Association]].

It was founded, initially as the Medical Officers Union, in 1954 by Dr Vincent Tabone.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Rudolph|first1=Uwe Jens|last2=Berg|first2=Warren G|title=Historical Dictionary of Malta|date=2010|publisher=Scarecrow Press|location=Maryland|isbn=9780810873902|pages=215}}</ref>

Mr. Gordon Caruana Dingli is the president of the Council of the association for 2014/6.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Council 2014 - 2016|url=http://www.mam.org.mt/council.htm|website=Medical Association of Malta|accessdate=20 December 2015}}</ref>

It organised a satellite meeting for the Commonwealth People’s Forum during the [[Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting 2015]] which was held in Malta in November 2015.  Sir [[Michael Marmot]] spoke on social inequality.<ref>{{cite news|title=‘Social inequality bad for our health’|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20151125/local/social-inequality-bad-for-our-health.593437|accessdate=20 December 2015|publisher=Times of Malta|date=25 November 2015}}</ref>

It opposes private sector involvement in the management of the Maltese health system.<ref>{{cite news|title=Doctors' union issues warning on government plans for private sector involvement|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20150714/local/doctors-union-issues-warning-on-government-plans-for-private-sector.576601|accessdate=20 December 2015|publisher=Times of Malta|date=14 July 2015}}</ref>

