[[File:Plan de Man poster.gif|thumb|right|Contemporary poster showing the Plan, portrayed as a fist, attacking big business, represented as an octopus coiled around the Belgian economy.]] The '''Labour Plan''' ({{lang-fr|Plan du Travail}}, {{lang-nl|Plan van de Arbeid}}), commonly known as the '''Plan De Man''' after its creator, was an economic policy devised in 1933 by the Belgian politician [[Henri De Man]] of the [[Belgian Labour Party]] (POB-BWP) to combat the economic situation experienced by Belgium in the aftermath of the [[Great Depression]]. The plan, described as a "Labour Plan", was one of the foremost examples of De Man's doctrine of "[[Planned economy|Planisme]]" (state planning).<ref>{{cite web|last=Boneau|first=Denis|title=Le planisme, une idéologie fasciste française|url=http://www.voltairenet.org/article15364.html|publisher=[[Voltaire Network]]|accessdate=3 July 2013}}</ref> The policy was aimed at "instilling a mixed economic system" by the creation of "a nationalized sector covering the organization of credit and the main industries which have already in reality been monopolized."<ref>{{cite book|last=Deruette|first=Serge|title=La Vie en Rose: Réalités de l'Histoire du Parti Socialiste en Belgique|year=1999|publisher=Aden|page=90}}</ref>
It was broadly similar to the [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]]'s 1933 "[[New Deal]]" in the United States and the later [[Social Democratic Workers' Party (Netherlands)|SDAP's]] 1935 "Plan of Work" in the Netherlands.
==Criticism== Despite the support of the POB-BWP, the plan was criticized by many left-wing commentators. [[Leon Trotsky]] derided the plan as "a plan to deceive the toilers" and "a renovated instrument of bourgeois-democratic conservatism."<ref name=Trotsky1>{{cite journal|last=Trotsky|first=Leon|authorlink=Leon Trotsky|title=Revisionism and Planning: The Revolutionary Struggle against Labor Fakers|journal=New International|date=January 1934|volume=11 [1945]|issue=2|url=http://www.marxists.org/archive/trotsky/1934/01/planning.htm}}</ref> Trotsky further attacked the plan in a January 1934 article, entitled ''Revisionism and Planning'', in the newspaper ''[[New International]]''.<ref name=Trotsky1/>
==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== *{{cite news|title=En avant pour le Plan du Travail|url=http://digital.amsab.be/pubs_serials/Le_Mouvement_Syndical_Belge_1918-1940/mouvsybe_1933/mouvsybe_1933_nr11.pdf|accessdate=3 July 2013|newspaper=Le Mouvement Syndical Belge|date=20 November 1933}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} *{{cite journal|last=Claeys van Haegendoren|first=Mieke|title=La pratique du planisme en Belgique|journal=[[Revue Européenne des Sciences Sociales]]|volume=12|number=31|year=1974|pages=131–42|jstor=40369390}}
