{{Unreferenced|date=June 2011}} {{Infobox company | name = Termoelectrica | logo = | caption = | type = State owned | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|2000}} | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Bucharest]] | location_country = [[Romania]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = Viorel Marian (CEO) | industry = [[Electricity]] | products = | services = | revenue = US$346&nbsp;million (2007) | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 1,683 (2006) | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.termoelectrica.ro}} | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Termoelectrica''' is a [[Romania]]n [[state-owned]] company, its shares being held by the [[Ministry of Economy and Commerce]] which has as main objective [[power generation]] with thermal power plants.
Termoelectrica owns three [[subsidiary|subsidiaries]] with a total installed capacity of 1,717 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] and an annual average power production of 5.910 [[TWh]], 9.64% of the total national output of [[Romania]]. {{cn|date=August 2017}}
