'''Youth in Asia''' constituted the largest youth population by region in 2015, numbering 718 million.<ref name=YouthPOP>{{cite web|url=http://www.un.org/esa/socdev/documents/youth/fact-sheets/YouthPOP.pdf|title=Population Facts: Youth population trends and sustainable development|date=May 2015|publisher=UN Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division}}</ref> The [[United Nations]] defines youth as persons aged 15 to 24 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/new/en/social-and-human-sciences/themes/youth/youth-definition/|title=Youth - Definition - United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization|website=www.unesco.org}}</ref> The number of youth in Asia is projected to decline to 619 million by 2060.

