{{For|the Hanka Paldum album|Čežnja (album)}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Yugoslavia}} "Čežnja" | image = | caption = | year = 1965 | country = Yugoslavia | artist = [[Vice Vukov]] | as = | with = | language = Croatian | languages = | composer = Julio Marić | lyricist = Žarko Roje | conductor = Radivoj Spasić | place = 12th | points = 2 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1965yu from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Život je sklopio krug | prev_link = Život je sklopio krug | next = Brez besed | next_link = Brez besed }}
'''"Čežnja"''' ("Longing") was the [[Yugoslavia]]n entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1965]], performed in [[Croatian Language|Croatian]] by [[Vice Vukov]].
The song was performed seventeenth on the night, following [[Finland]]'s [[Viktor Klimenko (singer)|Viktor Klimenko]] com "[[Aurinko laskee länteen]]" and preceding [[Switzerland]]'s [[Yovanna]] with "[[Non, à jamais sans toi]]". At the close of voting, it had received two points, placing 12th.
The song compares the elements of nature (clouds, waves) with his longing of his lover.
It was succeeded as [[Yugoslavia in the Eurovision Song Contest|Yugoslavian representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1966|1966 Contest]] by [[Berta Ambrož]] with "[[Brez besed]]".
